result.execSummary:
The defendant Craig S. Kytonen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery or Threat to Judge, Prosecutor, or Law Enforcement Officer, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.203(2).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Court questions DE regarding the plea. DA explains elements of charge.  Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist. records.addlTxt: Status hearing on May 25, 2022 at 10:00 am.

11:02 AM DA calls case and states appearancews. Defendant Craig S. Kytonen appeared via video from Price County Jail with attorney Kristopher R Ellis who appeared in person.  Karl J. Kelz appeared for the State of Wisconsin. DA Kelz calls witness Lieutenant Blain Peterson. Witness sworn. Direct questioning of the witness by DA Kelz. Witness identifies the defendant. No cross by Attorney Ellis. Statement by DA Kelz. Objection to bind over by Attorney Ellis. Court finds probable cause exists that a crime was committed and binds DE over for trial. Information filed, acknowledged by parties and reading waived. DE enters plea of NOT GUILTY to all counts.   Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled.
